The paper deals with the computation of the ergodic capacity of MIMO channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the maximization of a multilinear polynomial, which is a problem in optimization (cs.OH). The use of H-stable polynomials suggests a connection to algebraic complexity theory (cs.CC) or algebraic geometry (cs.AG). However, since the paper is primarily focused on the application of these concepts to the computation of the ergodic capacity of MIMO channels, we consider cs.SI (signal processing) and cs.NA (numerical analysis) to be more likely categories. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of a conjecture related to log-concavity, which is a topic in probability theory and statistics (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
